OWERRI – Governor Hope Uzodimma of Imo State has flagged-off the state’s Waste Management Agency operations in the state capital, and handed over 12 newly acquired trucks/pay-loaders and other working equipment to the Ministry of Social Welfare and Sanitation for effec­tive operations. The ceremony, which took place at the Hero Square, was described by the Governor as “a new dawn in the annals of the state’s approach to cleanliness through effective waste management.” The Governor said that the equip­ment was procured to enable the Minis­try of Social Welfare and Sanitation and the state’s Waste Management Agency to carry out their duties effectively and be able to keep Owerri and its enviros clean. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He used the opportunity to advise the citizens of Imo State to be partners in progress on waste management by be­ing careful and deploy the right attitude in the way they manage their waste, warning that they must ensure that ev­erything that comes out of their homes, considered as waste, goes into the waste bin box that has been provided for them. Uzodimma, however, warned that anybody found dropping waste on the road/street or scattering waste where they were not supposed to would be lia­ble to be arrested and prosecuted. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION